OL,3,CCalls to scrap trans inclusion
OL,4,Cguidance criticised as 'political'
OL,6,FThe St Clement representative argues
OL,7,FJersey should instead adopt the
OL,8,F"watchful waiting approach" - a more
OL,9,F"cautious non-interventionist" model
OL,10,Fput forward by the Cass Review.
OL,12,FThe Jersey proposition also considers
OL,13,Fthe views of the local Women's Rights
OL,14,FNetwork, who are unhappy with the
OL,15,Fcurrent guidance and safeguarding
OL,16,Fmeasures in the island's schools.
OL,18,FIt also follows a 2025 petition, which
OL,19,Fsaw more than 1,000 islanders call for
OL,20,Fthe Trans Inclusion Guidance to be
OL,21,Frevoked.
