OL,6,FRecommendations in the proposal
OL,8,FDeputy Bailhache's proposal argues
OL,9,Fcurrent "flaws" in the guidance
OL,10,Finclude allowing children who are
OL,11,Ftransitioning to choose which toilets
OL,12,Fthey wish to use, using the pronouns
OL,13,Frequested by transitioning children
OL,14,Fand teaching gender in science lessons.
OL,16,FHe writes: "Children should not be
OL,17,Fcompelled to use wrong-sex pronouns
OL,18,Fabout other pupils, nor should
OL,19,Fchildren be identified as 'trans'
OL,20,Fbecause that presupposes the outcome
OL,21,Fof the child's belief."
