OL,3,CCalls to scrap trans inclusion
OL,4,Cguidance criticised as 'political'
OL,6,FThe proposed guidance, drafted by
OL,7,FStephanie Davies-Arai, the founder of
OL,8,FTransgender Trend, suggests Jersey
OL,9,Fshould adopt "the default position" of
OL,10,Finforming parents if their child is
OL,11,Fquestioning their gender - unless
OL,12,Fthere's a "clear risk" to the child.
OL,14,FThe UK organisation describes itself
OL,15,Fas "advocating for evidence-based care
OL,16,Fof gender dysphoric children and
OL,17,Fscience-based teaching".
OL,19,FMs Davies-Arai was scheduled to speak
OL,20,Fat Highlands College last year, but
OL,21,Fthe talk was later cancelled.
