OL,6,FShe writes: "Children should never be
OL,7,Fexpected to be involved in decision-
OL,8,Fmaking about their own safeguarding.
OL,9,FIt is the adults' job to set
OL,10,Fsafeguarding policy.
OL,12,F"Children are not adults: we should
OL,13,Fnot confuse children's rights with
OL,14,Fadult rights."
