OL,4,Cguidance criticised as 'political'
OL,6,FThe current guidelines, issued to all
OL,7,FChildren, Young People, Education and
OL,8,FSkills (CYPES) staff and departments
OL,9,Fin March last year, state that
OL,10,Fchildren and young people "have a
OL,11,Fright to explore their identities, be
OL,12,Faccepted and change their minds".
OL,14,FAll staff are required to undertake
OL,15,Ftraining to understand terms such as
OL,16,Fcorrect pronouns and challenging
OL,17,Fgender stereotypes, and are expected
OL,18,Fto "listen openly and respectfully" to
OL,19,Fquestions or concerns without
OL,20,F"breaking the confidentiality" of
OL,21,Findividuals.
