OL,3,CCalls to scrap trans inclusion
OL,4,Cguidance criticised as 'political'
OL,6,F"Existing guidance already provides
OL,7,Fclear standards on behaviour, bullying
OL,8,Fprevention and collaborative
OL,9,Fdecisionmaking with families and
OL,10,Fprofessionals and explicitly excludes
OL,11,Fmedical decision-making from the remit
OL,12,Fof schools.
OL,14,F"The replacement document directs
OL,15,Fpractitioners to deprioritise the
OL,16,Fvoice of the child, an approach
OL,17,Ffundamentally at odds with Jersey's
OL,18,Fstatutory requirements, international
OL,19,Fconventions, and modern safeguarding
OL,20,Fpractice.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws        G11/12
